[SN]TITLE[SN]
Aamir Hussain named as fatal Sheffield road crash victim

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A motorist who died in a crash near Rotherham has been named by police.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Aamir Hussain, 22, from Rotherham, died in the collision on Bawtry Road at about 01:40 BST on Friday.
South Yorkshire Police appealed for anyone with information to come forward.
A force spokesman said police were keen to speak with anyone who may have seen a dark-coloured hatchback type car driving near to the crash scene.
